"The purpose of this study is to investigate the relationship among online retailing information quality, e-satisfaction, e-trust and young generation customer's commitment in mainland China. The study variables have considerable importance in e-tailers performance. The data were col- lected based on a sample of 383 students from Chinese universities during the first quarter of 2014. We used confirmatory factor analysis (CFA) and structural equation modeling (SEM) to evaluate the hypotheses about the relationship among model constructs. Thus, all the hypoth- eses developed in the study were positively confirmed except one. Therefore, the investigated variables are reinforcing the theory and previous research in this field. This study reveals inter- esting implications of information quality, e-satisfaction, e-trust and customers commitment that are useful to both academicians and practitioners."
